**Company Description**
**Our mission, your future**
 As a global network of trusted advisors, we create cutting\\-edge technological solutions to overcome today’s challenges and anticipate tomorrow’s needs. It all starts with the collaboration of a diverse team of passionate innovators, each driven to make a difference. Together, we challenge the status quo and push each other to new heights.




 Ready to make a significant impact on mission\\-critical mandates and shape the future through digital transformation and strategic consulting? Take your ambitions to the next level and discover your next exciting challenge with us!




**Your role, your impact**
 As an experienced Business Intelligence (BI) Developer, you’ll join our data and analytics team to deliver high\\-quality reporting, analytics, and data integration solutions using Microsoft Fabric, Power BI, and other Azure\\-based services. You’ll work across the full BI solution lifecycle, transforming data into actionable insights that drive strategic decision\\-making for our clients.




 You’ll collaborate closely with cross\\-functional and global delivery teams, applying best practices and developing standards while adapting to evolving business and technical requirements. This role offers the opportunity to work with advanced Microsoft data technologies in a dynamic environment backed by strong delivery support.




**Your day\\-to\\-day**
* Gather and analyze business requirements with stakeholders to define reporting and analytics needs;
* Design and develop KPIs, measures, dimensions, and data models to support business objectives;
* Source, transform, and integrate data from multiple systems into accessible formats using tools such as Power BI, Power Query, and Azure Data Factory;
* Build and optimize semantic models, calculations, and visualizations for performance and usability;
* Lead report design, data sourcing, and transformation efforts from concept to deployment;
* Develop Microsoft Fabric and Power BI solutions that align with governance and security standards;
* Collaborate with technical, functional, and PMO teams to ensure timely and quality delivery;
* Mentor junior team members on BI best practices;
* Track and report progress in designated project management systems.


**Keys to your success**
* Bachelor’s degree in computer science, information systems, or a related field;
* Proven experience designing and delivering BI and analytics solutions;
* Strong skills in data integration: T\\-SQL, Microsoft Fabric Pipelines, Spark Notebooks, SSIS, Azure Data Factory, Databricks, or equivalent;
* Strong skills in reporting and analytics: Power BI, Power Query, M, DAX, SSAS, SSRS, Excel;
* Proficiency in both cloud and on\\-premises reporting environments;
* Familiarity with Agile and Waterfall methodologies;
* Strong problem\\-solving skills and ability to translate requirements into technical solutions;
* Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication abilities.


**Extra edge**
* Expertise in transactional and dimensional data modelling for both traditional warehouses and modern lakehouse architectures;
* Experience with big data platforms, column\\-oriented datastores, and advanced analytics tools;
* Knowledge of Microsoft Dynamics AX or Dynamics 365 Finance \\& Operations;
* Exposure to data warehouse automation tools such as TimeXtender or Jet Data Manager;
* Understanding of cloud infrastructure architectures;
* Domain knowledge in manufacturing and supply chain processes.


**Language Skills**
* English: Proficient


**Our authenticity is our strength**
 The diversity of our backgrounds, experiences, thoughts and insights is our competitive advantage. We foster a collaborative environment rooted in our core values of respect, well\\-being, passion, trust, integrity and creativity. For us, diversity, equity and inclusion aren’t just buzzwords; they’re essential drivers of innovation and excellence, and powerful catalysts for inspiration and evolutionary ideas. The empowerment of our people is fundamental to being the trusted advisor to our clients. Join us in embracing our authenticity and in leveraging our unique perspectives to collectively build the future we all envision.




**An inclusive path to success**
 Fostering an environment where you can thrive starts with ensuring an accessible recruitment process. If you require any accommodations, we welcome you to contact us. For more information, please visit our accessibility page at https://www.alithya.com/en/accessibility .
